  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, the Summer Institute of Linguistics (SIL) International, often referred to as SIG (SIL International Global), does not typically operate hostels. SIL is a faith-based nonprofit organization that focuses on language development, translation, and literacy, particularly for minority languages. They often work in collaboration with universities, training centers, and field locations around the world.\n\nIf you are referring to a specific location or campus associated with SIL (e.g., the SIL International headquarters in Dallas, Texas, or one of their training centers), accommodations like dormitories or shared housing might be available for attendees of specific programs or events. However, these are not standard hostels in the traditional sense.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, I recommend contacting SIL International directly or visiting their official website to inquire about accommodation options for your specific needs. They can provide details about housing facilities available at their various locations.",
